                      <font face="Verdana" size="2" color="white"><span class="spnMessageText" id="msg"> In the scheme of things, I've heard that the pet chain of power goes like this<br /><br />Mage -&gt; Beastlord -&gt; Necro (far behind). <br /><br />I'm looking for a tough pet class with mana regen. I like the utility of the necro, but I can't get over the fact that all the upper level necros refer to him as the "paper tiger". <br /><br />Can we stand behind this pet for a bit? I know the situational pets are just that. I have searched the forums and come up with a few vague reference and the whole EoT vs. LoZ, but I'm more concerned about if the pet is worth it, or do we just become victims of the root-rot style of EQ. When I got a necro to 50 before, it was before Kunark, so I don't know how they hold up anywhere other than old world. <br /><br />Any help would be appreciated. /wave<br /><br />Geoffrin<br />Level 40 (and rising).<br />Level 57 Shaman<br />Level 52 Mage<br />Level 57 SK<br />Torv</span id="msg"></font>
