                    <tr>
                      <td valign="top" height="100%"><font face="Verdana" size="2" color="white"><span class="spnMessageText" id="msg"> Necro pets are very good and can stand up to a beating, just like any warrior they need a heal every once in awhile.<br /><br />I normally group with a 58 Cleric, and 53 Shaman and EoT has played MA on Umberhulk, Lightcrawlers in PoD, High Guardians in PoJ, Cliff Golems in OT, and Rats in DN.  This is with the Cleric using CH just like it was a tank.<br /><br />EoT can walk through HS with cleric/shaman buffs and he very rarely needs a heal.  The taunt is good and he keeps the mobs off of us.<br /><br />Will he get eaten alive if he doesn't have someone healing him? YES  <br />Will a warrior get eaten alive if he doesn't have someone healing him? YES<br />Will he hold off a 400+ hitting mob long enough for you to FD or gate? YES<br />Will he ever be as good as a well equiped tank? NO<br />Will he ever be as good/better than a poorly equiped tank? Most of the time<br /><br />I like the comment made earlier - Necro makes the pet - Pet makes the Magi/Bst.<br /><br />Just a note this is only with EoT as I do not have LoZ and my understand is LoZ is hands down better than EoT.<br /><br />"And may thee farewell, wherever thy fare!<br />Sislibik Underfoot<br /><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=255911" target="_blank">http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=255911</a><br /></span id="msg"></font><br><br></td>
