                      <td valign="top" height="100%"><font face="Verdana" size="2" color="white"><span class="spnMessageText" id="msg"> LoZ can tank most oldworld mobs with just necro healing. PoP-wise, it will need a proper healer, ideally a cleric. An Aegoed LoZ  with a cleric backing it up has no problem tanking underbulks in PoD. Doesn't even eat up huge amounts of mana to keep it healed. With a shaman to slow, all it needs is Heroic Bond to tank.<br /><br />Mage pets might do more damage or have other abilities. But mages aren't as versatile as necros nor do they regen mana at anywhere near the same rate.<br /><br />Beastlord pets have all sorts of aggro-enhancing procs and various buffs. But, again, beastlords aren't as versatile as necros.<br /><br />Tenaiya Soulscorcher</span id="msg"></font><br><br></td>
